   <sex value="M"/>
   <note type="biography">
      <p>Birth: Redland, near Bristol, Gloucestershire, England (27 June 1786)</p>
      <p>Death: Berkeley Square, London (03 June 1869)</p>
      <p>Burial: Kensal Green cemetery, London</p>
      
      <p>Education: Westminster School; Trinity College, Cambridge. BA (1808), MA (1811)</p>
      <p>Career: Partner in Whitbread and Company, Brewers, London; committed to Newgate for his pamphlet "A trifling mistake" (December 1819-February 1820); MP; Privy Councillor; held several government offices; was a friend of Lord Byron</p>
      <p>Honours: Baron 1851; KCB 1852</p>
      
      <p>Membership: Fellow</p>
      <p>Election Date: 19/05/1814</p>
